title: Unable to install new update
body:
Thanks for opening this issue, and thanks for using DeepLabCut (we hope you are enjoying it ;). Please fill out the template completely, including the full "traceback" and input code that you ran to hit this error. **Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version** Windows 10, DeepLabCut 2.2rc1 Please complete the following information about your system: OS: Windows 10 DeepLabCut Version: 2.2 Anaconda env used: dlc-winGPU **Describe the problem** When I used the headless install update for the newest version, it installed but now trying to import deeplabcut it gives me this error and is not doing anything. I tried changing directories to see if that would help but to no avail. I have no clue what 'dataclasses' refers to. I had a prior trained network on here and have the old config saved for a successful training and tracking session but I'm worried if I reinstall, will I lose all my data? Moreover, what caused this error to occur? Also when i tried using the pip install for the new GUI for 2.2rc1 it did not work either but said an invalid internal requirement?
